.SH NAME
Bitcoin::Crypto::PSBT::FieldType \- PSBT field types
.SH SYNOPSIS
.IX Header "SYNOPSIS"
.Vb 1
\&        use Bitcoin::Crypto::PSBT::FieldType;
\&
\&        my $type = Bitcoin::Crypto::PSBT::FieldType\->get_field_by_name(\*(AqPSBT_IN_OUTPUT_INDEX\*(Aq);
.Ve
.SH DESCRIPTION
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
This is both a library of field types and a small struct\-like class for types.
.PP
An anonymous instance of this class can be created when a non\-defined field type is encountered.
.SH INTERFACE
.IX Header "INTERFACE"
.SS Attributes
.IX Subsection "Attributes"
\fIname\fR
.IX Subsection "name"
.PP
\&\fBRequired in the constructor.\fR Name of the field type defined in BIP174.
.PP
\fIcode\fR
.IX Subsection "code"
.PP
\&\fBRequired in the constructor.\fR Code of the field type defined in BIP174.
.PP
\fImap_type\fR
.IX Subsection "map_type"
.PP
\&\fBAvailable in the constructor.\fR A map type this field belongs to. If not
passed, it will be guessed from "name". Map types are defined as constants in
Bitcoin::Crypto::Constants.
.PP
\fIserializer\fR
.IX Subsection "serializer"
.PP
\&\fBAvailable in the constructor.\fR A coderef which will be used to do DWIM
serialization of the value for easier handling. If not passed, a simple coderef
will be installed which will only coerce format descriptions into bytestrings.
.PP
\fIdeserializer\fR
.IX Subsection "deserializer"
.PP
\&\fBAvailable in the constructor.\fR A coderef which will be used to do DWIM
deserialization of the value, the reverse of "serializer".
.PP
\fIkey_serializer\fR
.IX Subsection "key_serializer"
.PP
\&\fBAvailable in the constructor.\fR A coderef which will be used to do DWIM
serialization of the key for easier handling. If not passed, a simple coderef
will be installed which will only coerce format descriptions into bytestrings.
.PP
\fIkey_deserializer\fR
.IX Subsection "key_deserializer"
.PP
\&\fBAvailable in the constructor.\fR A coderef which will be used to do DWIM
deserialization of the key, the reverse of "key_serializer".
.PP
\fIvalidator\fR
.IX Subsection "validator"
.PP
\&\fBAvailable in the constructor.\fR A coderef which will be used to validate the
value. It will be passed deserialized key (if available) and value. It should
throw a string exception if it encounters a problem. This exception will be
then turned to \f(CW\*(C`Bitcoin::Crypto::Exception::PSBT\*(C'\fR. The return value will be
ignored.
.PP
\&\fIpredicate:\fR \f(CW\*(C`has_validator\*(C'\fR
.PP
\fIkey_data\fR
.IX Subsection "key_data"
.PP
\&\fBAvailable in the constructor.\fR Key data of the field type. It should be a
string describing what is the effect of deserialization and what the serializer
expects. It may be undefined if the field does not support extra key data.
.PP
\&\fIpredicate:\fR \f(CW\*(C`has_key_data\*(C'\fR
.PP
\fIvalue_data\fR
.IX Subsection "value_data"
.PP
\&\fBRequired in the constructor.\fR Value data of the field type. It should be a
string describing what is the effect of deserialization and what the serializer
expects.
.PP
\fIversion_status\fR
.IX Subsection "version_status"
.PP
\&\fBRequired in the constructor.\fR A hash reference, where keys are PSBT versions
and values are string, either \f(CW\*(C`required\*(C'\fR or \f(CW\*(C`available\*(C'\fR.
