.Ve
.PP
Returns a field type with a given \f(CW$code\fR for \f(CW$map_type\fR.
.PP
If no such field is defined, a new unknown field type will be created.
.PP
\fIget_field_by_name\fR
.IX Subsection "get_field_by_name"
.PP
.Vb 1
\&        $type = $class\->get_field_by_name($name)
.Ve
.PP
Returns a field type with a given \f(CW$name\fR.
.PP
If no such field is defined, an exception will be thrown. Unknown field type
cannot be created like in "get_field_by_code", because code is a required
part of a field, while name is only informatory.
.PP
